19/11/2003
ANKARA, Turkey -- Fatih Karaca, chairman of the Supreme Board of Radio and Television, said Tuesday (18 November) that draft legislation allowing broadcasting in languages and dialects commonly used in daily life has been submitted to the cabinet.
He added that permission to broadcast in mother tongues would be granted to national TV and radio stations upon request.
The legislation is compatible with EU requirements regarding minority rights.
(Anadolu Agency, NTV - 18/11/03)
